rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: Schema version
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: version

rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: Prefix URI map
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: prefix
primary_key
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: True means that this serves as a unique identifier

Additional info on how a slot is used in the context of a class. Many slots may be re-used across different classes, but the meaning of the slot may be refined by context. For example, a generic association model may use slots subject/predicate/object with generic semantics and minimal constraints. When this is subclasses, e.g. to disease-phenotype associations then slot_usage may specify both local naming (e.g. subject=disease) and local constraints
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: slot_usage

rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: The combination of is_a plus defining slots form a genus-differentia definition, or the set of necessary and sufficient conditions that can be transformed into an OWL equivalence axiom
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: defining_slots

rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: definition base class
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: definition
note
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: Notes about an element

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: slot definition
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: A property or slot

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: required
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: If true slot must have at least one value

used to indicate membership of a term in a defined subset of biolink terms used for a particular domain or application (e.g. the translator_minimal subset holding the minimal set of predicates used in a translator knowledge graph)
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: in_subset
object_property
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: true means that this slot is part of the formal definition of a class

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: flags
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: State information and other details

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: domain
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: The class to which this slot applies.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: close_matches
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: a list of terms from different schemas or terminology systems that have a semantically similar but not strictly equivalent, broader, or narrower meaning. Such terms often describe the same general concept from different ontological perspectives (e.g. drug as a type of chemical entity versus drug as a type of role borne by a chemical entity).
Used only as a mixin -- cannot be instantiated on its own.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: mixin
inlined
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: if true then the value of this slot is inlined (i.e. a nested object) rather linked by key

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: exact_matches
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: a list of terms from different schemas or terminology systems that have strictly equivalent meanings.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: source
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: the source of description or other element

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: element
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: root of all described things
list of class or slot definitions that are combined to create the union class
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: class definition union_of
identifier
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: True means that this slot must be unique across the collection of slots
types defined in schema
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: types
local name
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: the nsname (sans ':' for a given prefix)

specifies single-inheritance between classes and slots. While multiple inheritance is not allowed, mixins can be provided effectively providing the same thing. The semantics are the same when translated to formalisms that allow MI (e.g. RDFS/OWL). When translating to a SI framework (e.g. java classes, python classes) then is_a is used. When translating a framework without polymorphism (e.g. json-schema, solr document schema) then is_a and mixins are recursively unfolded
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: class definition is_a
symmetric
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: Symmetric slot
id of the schema that the element was derived from. Supplied by the loader.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: from_schema
alt description
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: Attributed description

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: comment
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: Comment about an element
Version of the metamodel used to load the schema. Supplied by the loader
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: metamodel_version
slots
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: list of slot names that are applicable to a class. slots are by default inherited over is_a and mixins.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: source_file_size
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: size in bytes of the source of the schema. Supplied by the loader

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: class definition
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: A class or interface

specifies single-inheritance between classes and slots. While multiple inheritance is not allowed, mixins can be provided effectively providing the same thing. The semantics are the same when translated to formalisms that allow MI (e.g. RDFS/OWL). When translating to a SI framework (e.g. java classes, python classes) then is_a is used. When translating a framework without polymorphism (e.g. json-schema, solr document schema) then is_a and mixins are recursively unfolded
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: is_a

rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: A collection of definitions
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: schema definition

rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: Additional prefixes to be added to the context beyond those fetched from prefixcommons in id_prefixes
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: prefixes

rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: Ontolgy property which this is a subclass of. Not to be confused with is_a which links datamodel classes
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: subclass_of
source_file
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: name, uri or description of the source of the schema. Supplied by the loader

a list of terms from different schemas or terminology systems that have comparable meaning. These may include terms that are precisely equivalent, broader or narrower in meaning, or otherwise semantically related but not equivalent from a strict ontological perspective.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: mappings
class definition mixins
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: List of definitions to be mixed in. Targets may be any definition of the same type

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: slot definition is_a
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: specifies single-inheritance between classes and slots. While multiple inheritance is not allowed, mixins can be provided effectively providing the same thing. The semantics are the same when translated to formalisms that allow MI (e.g. RDFS/OWL). When translating to a SI framework (e.g. java classes, python classes) then is_a is used. When translating a framework without polymorphism (e.g. json-schema, solr document schema) then is_a and mixins are recursively unfolded
a name that is used in the singular form
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: singular_name
range
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: The slot type. Can be any class or type

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: values_from
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: identifies the possible uri's of the range

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: examples
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: Example of usage for a slot or class

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: abstract
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: An abstract class is a high level class or slot that is typically used to group common slots together and is generally not instantiated. When generating golr-views, abstract classes are ignored
the default type if range is omitted
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: default_type
multivalued
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: If true slot can have many values
a list of terms from different schemas or terminology systems that have a narrower, more specific meaning. Narrower terms are typically shown as children in a hierarchy or tree.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: narrower_matches
prefix uri
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: A URI associated with a given prefix
A type definition
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: type definition
example
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: example of usage

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: description
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: a description

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: imports
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: A list of modules that are imported into the schema
date that the schema was loaded/generated. Supplied by the loader
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: generation_date

rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: List of definitions to be mixed in. Targets may be any definition of the same type
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: slot definition mixins
id
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: a globally unique id or url for a schema

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: default_curi_maps
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: List of prefixcommon biocontexts to be fetched to resolve id_prefixes and inline prefix variables
a unique key that identifies a slot, type or class in a schema
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: name

rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: A name to be assigned to the slot in implementations that is different that its type. The primary use for this is to allow class AND schema definitions to both have "slots" where one inline and the other a reference
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: alias

rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: collection of slot definitions in a schema
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: slot definitions
apply_to
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: Used to extend an existing class definition. For example, if we have a core schema where a gene has two slots for identifier and symbol, and we have a specialized schema for my_organism where we wish to add a slot systematic_name, we can avoid subclassing by defining a class gene_my_organism, adding the slot to this class, and then adding an apply_to pointing to the gene class. The new slot will be 'injected into' the gene class.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: local_names
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: map from local identifier to slot
license for the schema
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: license
source_file_date
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: modification date of the source of the schema. Supplied by the loader
For any denormalized slot, this represents the tree or graph path used to generate the denormalized form
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: path
slot definition union_of
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: list of class or slot definitions that are combined to create the union class
default and base prefix -- used for ':' identifiers, @base and @vocab
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: default_prefix
classes
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: classes defined in schema
List of definitions to be mixed in. Targets may be any definition of the same type
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: mixins

rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: Ontolgy property which this is a subproperty of
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: subproperty_of
inherited
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: True means that the slot is an essential attribute of the container -- that the slot is carried across is_a and slot_usage paths
list of class or slot definitions that are combined to create the union class
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: union_of
broader_matches
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: a list of terms from different schemas or terminology systems that have a broader, more general meaning. Broader terms are typically shown as parents in a hierarchy or tree.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: inverse
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: used to indicate the inverse of a slot (e.g. 'expresses' is the inverse predicate of 'expressed in')
a builtin ('string', 'integer', 'float', 'double', 'boolean', 'time', 'uri') or another type definition
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: typeof
alt_description_text
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: text of an alternate description
